Moiraine is…okay, I guess? I don’t like her powers being realized via interpretive dance, but whatever. The actor playing Lan seems competent but holy shit, Lan should be HUGE. Like the dude should be built like The Rock, his size needs to contrast Mouraine’s small stature.

What they did to Perrin (my favorite character) was an absolute travesty. I know WHY they did it, but holy shit that is NOT the way to go when you’re trying to visually show why he keeps himself tightly controlled. Just a REALLY bad and needlessly grim choice all around.

That said, it’s a pilot. Things could improve significantly. I’m gonna keep watching & I may come to love the casting—even Rand—once these characters are given a chance to shine. Despite an action-heavy third act there just wasn’t much there, beyond Matt’s subplot.

The casting is diverse, which is the best thing about it—but simultaneously it’s also aggressively milquetoast. Rand is possibly the worst example of this. The actor and costuming has some real “Manikin Skywalker” energy to it. So much so that it almost feels like a choice.

Judging from the #WheelOfTime pilot alone—It’s not BAD by any stretch of the imagination but also lacks passion and specificity. Expect every scene to be realized in the most obvious and bland way possible. There’s no “style” to anything, it’s all empty calories.

The locations in #wheeloftime are remarkable. The direction, casting, and special effects are…less so.

Jury is out on the writing & acting.
